DEFINITIONS

"Seat" means each distinct human individual who operates, administers, deploys,
or accesses the Software or its outputs on behalf of you or your organization.
Automated agents, workers, or processes do not count as Seats in themselves; they
are attributed to the Seat of the human individual on whose behalf they act.

"Production use" means any use other than for personal experimentation,
evaluation, development, or testing.

